<parts.title>2 zw/ foto's: 1 van het geheel, 1 van de achterzijde; 1 afbeelding in kleur van het geheel in de catalogus.</parts.title>
<parts.title>Description des tableaux des pièces de sculpture, que renferme la Gallerie de son altesse François Joseph chef et prince regnant de la maison Liechtenstein etc.etc., Vienne, chez Jean Thom nob. de Trattnern, imprimeur et libraire de la cour, 1780, p. 98: Breughel dit le Paysan, 282. Une belle tête de paysan. Peinte sur bois, hauteur 9 pouces, sur autant de largeur.</parts.title>
<parts.title>[Jacob von] Falke, Katalog Fürstlich Liechtensteinischen Bildergalerie im Gartenpalais der Rossau zu Wien, Wien: Verlag von Miethke & Wawra, 1873, p. 128, N° 1110.</parts.title>
<parts.title>p. 89 [sic] Amongst the papers of the Antwerp art dealer FORCHOUDT, too, so F. Grossmann informs me, there are several references to such pictures: Oct. 18, 1674, the members of the Forchoudt family living in Vienna recieve from Antwerp: "N° 49. 1 Tronie van Bruegel."[scan]</parts.title>
<parts.title>Heads by Bruegel, Oct. 18, 1674 the members of the Forchoudt family living in Vienna receive from Antwerp [...]; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'This note given to L. Koetser 16-12-59. Glück, German edition, p. 90f.'</parts.title>
<parts.title>Korte inhoud: Op vraag van FG uitleg over de betekenis van het woord 'tronie.'</parts.title>
<parts.title>[recto] In favour: Difference of eyes, the left one round. Technique to be studied. The surface coarser than Munich woman, but hair looks good, cf. Blind Man, pl. 151. Does Bruegel ever paint such a  "(*) mouth line" technique. Isn't the form too simple compared with e.g. pl. 137. (*) cf. [onleesbaar] in pl.130. Colour of background like in the Munich Head. For the mouth line, cf. King left border in London Adoration & painter in the Albertina drawing, T. 118.; [verso]The background more brown grey than in repr. A system of pink lines up cheek.The shadows in cross hatchings very fine like with feather in brown ink.[scan]</parts.title>
<parts.title>Bruegel. Head with Koetser, Nov. Dec. 1959, Sold to Italy. Paint pink lines [schema] going down to chin. Neck also pink. On his right cheek on yellowish ground same parallel strokes  leading down from right to left on this some broad pink (by restorer?) parts with [onleesbaar], (brown spots) greenish Hair brown -Nose red [..] [scan]</parts.title>
<parts.title>Korte inhoud: [Taal, Duits] Informatie over de afmetingen van het werk verkocht door Koetser 1959.[scan]</parts.title>
